        sdg1_energy_poverty_def_label: `Definitions of Energy Poverty:`,
        sdg1_energy_poverty_def_text: `Energy poverty refers to the condition of individuals, families or groups that do not have normal and regular access to the sources of energy needed to meet their primary needs (cooking, heating/ventilation, lighting) for example, due to buildings poorly insulated from the cold or heat or due to unsuitability or price of energy resources.`,
